## Why this restrictive license?

KL Sync scrapes KL University's ERP system without official API access or permission. This creates a legal gray area — the university could request it be shut down at any time. 

A permissive license (like MIT or Apache) would allow anyone to freely fork, rebrand, and host it elsewhere on the public internet, which could easily escalate the legal risk and footprint back to the original author.

This restrictive license keeps the project under control and lets me remain transparent about the risks. If the university formally endorses this project or provides official API access in the future, we will eagerly relicense it under something more open.
